<Base
  title="Primorum — We Find $100K+ in AI-Automatable Operations"
  description="Primorum finds at least $100K in annual savings from AI-automatable processes in your business — or we tell you there's nothing worth doing. The audit is free. Start today."
>
  <p class="eyebrow">Primorum</p>

  <h1 class="hero">
    We'll find $100K+ in automatable operations &mdash; or tell you there's
    nothing worth doing.
  </h1>

  <p class="lede">
    Most businesses above $2M in revenue are carrying $100K&ndash;500K in
    operational overhead that AI can eliminate today. Not in five years. Not
    after a six-figure digital transformation. Right now. The bottleneck isn't
    the technology &mdash; it's knowing which processes to automate, which tools
    to use, and what it actually costs vs. what it actually returns. That's what
    we do.
  </p>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>What we believe</h2>

  <ul class="bets">
    <li>
      <p class="label">System 2, not System 1</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Frontier labs build the fast, pattern-matching models. We build the
        deliberate verification layer that makes them dependable. The models do
        the thinking; we supply the judgment.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Dependability is the scarce resource</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Raw model capability is commoditizing. The thing customers actually pay
        for &mdash; the thing that isn't commoditizing &mdash; is knowing the
        outcome will be delivered.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">You pay for outcomes, not tokens</p>
      <p class="claim">
        A model call costs a fraction of a cent. A guaranteed outcome is worth
        thousands. The premium is for the verification and the commitment to
        deliver &mdash; not the inference.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">We diagnose before we prescribe</p>
      <p class="claim">
        We don't sell AI. We find operational waste and then prescribe fixes.
        The audit comes first because prescribing without diagnosing is
        malpractice &mdash; in medicine and in business.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Token capital compounds</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Every workflow we deploy generates training signal unique to your firm.
        The system gets better with each use. You're not buying a one-time
        automation project &mdash; you're making the first deposit in a
        compounding institutional asset. The automations pay back this year.
        The learning loop pays back forever.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>The learning loop</h2>

  <p class="lede">
    This transition is different from any previous platform shift. In the past,
    we used digital systems to enhance human capital. This is the first time we
    can create a genuine cognitive loop between people and digital systems.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    Every company is going to have to build what we think of as
    <strong>human capital</strong> and <strong>token capital</strong>. Human
    capital is the knowledge, judgment, relationships, and pattern recognition
    of your people. Token capital is the AI capability your firm builds and
    owns &mdash; the systems, the training signal, the institutional knowledge
    encoded in workflows that improve with every use.
  </p>

  <ol class="steps">
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">1</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">Your people make judgments.</p>
        <p>
          Every decision, correction, and pattern your team recognizes is a
          training signal. Human capital is the driver. Without human direction,
          you have compute running in circles.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">2</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">The system learns from them.</p>
        <p>
          Private evaluations &mdash; measured against your actual business
          outcomes, not public benchmarks &mdash; tell the system whether it's
          improving where it matters. Private reinforcement environments let
          models grow stronger on real traces from inside your organization.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">3</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">Token capital compounds.</p>
        <p>
          Every improved workflow generates better training signal, which
          accelerates the accumulation of tacit knowledge unique to your firm.
          You can offload a task, or even a job, but you can never offload your
          learning. The future of the firm is the ability to compound that
          learning across people and AI.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">4</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">Human capital becomes more valuable.</p>
        <p>
          As token capital grows, human capital does not become less valuable.
          It becomes more valuable. Your people set more ambitious goals, connect
          dots across domains, and recognize patterns that matter most &mdash;
          while the system handles what it has already learned.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>The audit: we find the number, or we say so</h2>

  <p class="lede">
    The free audit is not a discovery call dressed up as a deliverable. It's a
    concrete report that identifies every AI-automatable process in your
    operations, ranks them by revenue impact, and attaches real cost and return
    estimates.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    If the total annual savings add up to less than $100K, we'll tell you that.
    You'll have lost 30 minutes. If they add up to more &mdash; and they usually
    do &mdash; you'll have a phased roadmap to capturing it, built by people who
    can build it for you.
  </p>

  <p class="cta-block">
    <a class="cta" href="mailto:engage@primorum.ai?subject=Free%20AI%20Operations%20Audit">Request your free audit &rarr;</a>
    <span class="cta-note">You'll hear back within one business day. No cost. No commitment.</span>
  </p>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>Where the $100K usually hides</h2>

  <p class="lede">
    Across the audits we've scoped, the money clusters in a predictable set of
    operational layers. These are the seams where human capital leaks into
    repetitive work instead of compounding into institutional knowledge.
  </p>

  <ul class="bets">
    <li>
      <p class="label">Customer operations</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Onboarding, support triage, follow-up sequences, churn detection. AI
        handles the first two tiers of customer interaction today &mdash; your
        team handles the exceptions, not the queue.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Revenue workflows</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Lead qualification, proposal generation, pipeline management, renewal
        timing. AI compresses sales cycles without adding headcount. A CRM
        populated by machines, not by your reps on Friday afternoon.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Back-office processes</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Invoice processing, expense categorization, compliance checks, report
        generation. AI eliminates the manual stitching between tools that eats
        10&ndash;20 hours per person per week.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Data &amp; reporting</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Data extraction from documents, cross-system reconciliation, dashboard
        population, anomaly detection. AI turns scattered data into decisions
        without a human spending Monday morning in Excel.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Communications</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Email drafting, meeting summaries, stakeholder updates, internal
        knowledge retrieval. AI keeps information moving without your best
        people becoming full-time information routers.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="label">Hiring &amp; people ops</p>
      <p class="claim">
        Candidate screening, onboarding document generation, policy Q&A,
        training material adaptation. AI scales the people function so your HR
        team stops doing data entry and starts doing people work.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>What you get</h2>

  <ul class="rules">
    <li>
      <p class="num">01</p>
      <p class="rule">A dollar figure.</p>
      <p>
        Total annual savings identified, broken down by process. Not a range.
        Not a projection. A specific number with the assumptions visible.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="num">02</p>
      <p class="rule">Named tools and build estimates.</p>
      <p>
        For each process, we name the software &mdash; off-the-shelf, custom, or
        API-integrated &mdash; and what it costs to implement. No "AI platform"
        hand-waving.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="num">03</p>
      <p class="rule">A phased roadmap.</p>
      <p>
        What to automate first, second, and third. Ordered by return on effort:
        highest savings, lowest implementation cost, least operational
        disruption. Start capturing savings in weeks, not quarters.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="num">04</p>
      <p class="rule">The honest answer.</p>
      <p>
        If we can't find $100K, you get that answer in writing &mdash; with the
        analysis that backs it up &mdash; and you owe nothing. We'd rather build
        trust than book a dead engagement.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>How it works</h2>

  <ol class="steps">
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">1</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">You reach out.</p>
        <p>
          Send a note describing your business. Size, industry, what feels
          operationally heavy. A paragraph is enough.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">2</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">We talk (30 minutes).</p>
        <p>
          A focused call to map your operational landscape &mdash; your tools,
          your workflows, where the friction lives. We come prepared with
          industry-specific questions. You don't need to prep anything.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p class="step-num">3</p>
      <div>
        <p class="step-title">You get the audit.</p>
        <p>
          Within a week: the dollar figure, the named tools, the build
          estimates, the phased roadmap. You decide whether to commission us to
          build it, build it yourself, or do nothing. No pressure. No follow-up
          sequence. The report speaks for itself.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2>If the number is there, we can build it</h2>

  <p class="lede">
    When the audit finds $100K+ &mdash; and it usually does &mdash; we can
